  attackReactions:
  - Hold the line! My bones still serve their oath!
  - Rattle on, cursed frame! We fight with honor!
  - I shall not yield while even one bone remains!
  - For my fallen kingdom, I strike!
  - Come then, knave! Test your steel against the dead!
  - My ancient wrath is far from spent!
  - These old bones still remember war!
  - I was forged in battle long before your time!
  - Stand fast! The grave has not claimed me yet!
  - You face not a corpse, but a knight eternal!
  healReactions:
  - So, you hide behind trinkets and tonics? Pathetic.
  - "Healing yourself? Have you no warrior\u2019s pride?"
  - Coward! Face me blade to blade!
  - You delay the inevitable with borrowed strength.
  - A heal item? Hah! Even now, you fear defeat.
  - Such desperate sorcery will not save you.
  - You patch your wounds, yet your courage still bleeds.
  - Consume all you wish, doom still marches toward you.
  - You mend your flesh, but not your weakness.
  - Rely on your little remedies. I shall simply strike again.
  fleeFailReactions:
  - Did you truly believe you could flee from the dead?
  - Where are you going, coward? The battle is here!
  - Nice try, meatbag... your retreat ends now.
  - No one escapes my cursed watch.
  - Run if you wish, your fear only amuses me.
  - There is no fleeing from a knight bound by death.
  - Stand and fight! Your legs will not save you!
  - You cannot outrun judgment.
  - Back to the battlefield with you, craven fool!
  - The grave is patient... and so am I.
  deathReactions:
  - I have failed... my kingdom... once more...
